      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD3S is a superlative example of rotary performance, featuring the iconic 13B-REW engine with its complex sequential twin-turbocharger setup in peak operational condition. The powertrain delivers seamless boost transitions and is paired with a crisp 5-speed manual gearbox and a Torsen limited-slip differential for optimal torque distribution. The chassis remains factory-spec, utilizing aluminum double-wishbone suspension components to maintain its legendary 50/50 weight balance. Recent diagnostic logs show exceptional compression across all rotor faces, and the vacuum-line 'rat's nest' has been meticulously maintained to prevent heat soak. With flawless original paint and a pristine cockpit, this vehicle offers a mechanically pure driving experience for the serious enthusiast.",
